# Local Dev Workflow

## Two modes — know which one you need

### Mode 1: Daily development (default)
Use this for all feature work. Hot-reload, Postgres via Docker, seed scripts work.

```bash
./bin/dev db             # start dev Postgres (first time only — persists via volume)
npm run dev              # from project root — starts backend + frontend together
```

- Backend: uvicorn with `--reload` on http://localhost:8000
- Frontend: Vite dev server on http://localhost:3000
- DB: Postgres via `docker-compose.dev.yml` on localhost:5432
- `./bin/dev server` and `./bin/dev seed` auto-start Postgres if not running
- Seed realistic data (run once after first start):

```bash
./bin/dev seed
```

### Mode 2: Production verification (before deploy)
Use this to confirm the Docker image builds and runs correctly against Postgres + Redis.

```bash
docker compose up --build    # nginx/certbot excluded via override profile
```

- Backend: http://localhost:8000 (Postgres, Redis connected)
- No hot-reload. Rebuild with `docker compose up --build` after code changes.
- `devtools/` scripts are intentionally excluded from the Docker image — run seeds in Mode 1.
- Docker build context is the workspace root: `docker build -f backend/Dockerfile .`

## Key ports
| Service  | Mode 1 (native) | Mode 2 (Docker) |
|----------|-----------------|-----------------|
| Backend  | :8000           | :8000           |
| Frontend | :3000           | —               |
| Postgres | :5432           | :5433           |

## Common dev commands

All commands run from the project root via `./bin/dev`:

```bash
./bin/dev test [args]      # run all tests (backend + frontend)
./bin/dev test:be [args]   # backend tests only (pytest)
./bin/dev test:fe          # frontend tests only (vitest)
./bin/dev test:e2e [args]  # Playwright e2e tests
./bin/dev lint             # ruff lint all Python
./bin/dev fmt              # ruff format all Python
./bin/dev lint:fe          # ESLint frontend
./bin/dev fmt:fe           # Prettier frontend
./bin/dev commit           # commitizen conventional commit
./bin/dev server           # backend only (no frontend)
./bin/dev ui               # frontend only (no backend)
./bin/dev seed [args]      # run seed_realistic
./bin/dev eval [args]      # run LLM evals
./bin/dev db               # start dev Postgres only
./bin/dev db:stop          # stop dev Postgres
```

Never suggest `pip`, `python -m pytest`, or `ruff` directly. All Python execution goes through `uv` (via `./bin/dev`). The project uses `uv` workspaces — the root `pyproject.toml` manages dev deps, `backend/pyproject.toml` has production deps only.

## Monorepo layout

```
sku-ops/
├── backend/          # deployable app + its tests
│   └── tests/        # backend unit/integration/api tests
├── frontend/         # React SPA (co-located unit tests in src/__tests__/)
├── tests/e2e/        # cross-stack Playwright tests
├── devtools/         # seeds, evals, scripts — not deployed
├── bin/dev           # unified CLI
└── pyproject.toml    # uv workspace root (dev deps, ruff, pytest, commitizen)
```

Each deployable owns its tests. Devtools live at the workspace root. The Docker image contains zero test or devtools code — `backend/tests/` is excluded via `.dockerignore`, devtools is structurally outside the `COPY backend/` layer, and `uv sync --no-dev` skips test deps.

## Frontend always proxies /api → localhost:8000
Configured in `frontend/vite.config.js`. Works with both modes as long as backend is on :8000.
